## PLAN ##

To check if t is an anagram of s, we can follow these steps:
1. Check if the lengths of s and t are equal. If not, return False.
2. Convert both s and t into lists of characters.
3. Sort both lists.
4. Check if both sorted lists are equal. If yes, return True. Otherwise, return False.

The time complexity of this approach is O(n log n), where n is the length of the input strings.
